## 1. DATABASE LAYER (NoteRow & noteDb Interface)

**File:** `/Users/anotonio.silva/antonio/lol/src/utils/database.ts` (lines 40-628)

### NoteRow Type
```typescript
export interface NoteRow {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  content: string;
  created_at: string;
  updated_at: string;
}
```

### noteDb API (lines 527-628)
The `noteDb` object follows the same pattern as other database abstractions with dual-mode support (Tauri DB + localStorage fallback):

```typescript
export const noteDb = {
  async getAll(): Promise<NoteRow[]>
  async getById(id: string): Promise<NoteRow | null>
  async insert(note: NoteRow): Promise<void>
  async update(id: string, updates: Partial<Omit<NoteRow, 'id' | 'updated_at'>>): Promise<void>
  async delete(id: string): Promise<void>
  async search(query: string, limit = 50): Promise<NoteRow[]>
}
```

**Key patterns:**
- Platform-aware: checks `isTauri` to use SQLite or localStorage
- `getById()` is unique to notes (useful for detail view)
- `update()` signature excludes `id` and `updated_at` (auto-managed)
- Search uses LIKE queries for title/content
- Validation function: `isNoteRowArray()` (line 207)

